<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="831" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d831">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/31290</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Apostolic Delegate at Washington</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cicognani</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 492/42</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-10">August 10,
                                1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Welles</hi>: Allow me to thank you most
                            kindly for your esteemed communication of August 8th with reference to
                            the proposed declaration of Rome as an open city. The contents of your
                            message were immediately transmitted to the Cardinal Secretary of State.
                            I shall be honored to present any further considerations on this matter
                            which His Eminence may eventually transmit.</p>
                        <p>Assuring you of my deep appreciation of your prompt reply to my letter of
                            August 7th, and with sentiments of high personal regard [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">A. G. Cicognani</hi>
                            </signed>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Archbishop of Laodicea</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>